Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at John R. Lewis High School in Springfield, Virginia on Gun Violence Awareness Day. She emphasized the need for gun violence prevention measures and highlighted the impact of gun violence on communities, particularly marginalized groups. Harris called for common-sense gun reform, including background checks and red-flag laws, and renewing the assault weapons ban. She also stressed that supporting the Second Amendment and passing gun safety laws are not mutually exclusive. Harris credited the activism of young leaders in pushing for change and mentioned the bipartisan gun safety legislation passed in 2020. She urged continued advocacy to ensure that the voices of students, parents, and teachers are heard. Harris concluded by emphasizing the importance of civil rights and the responsibility of young leaders to join the fight against gun violence.